summary: A U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing 58 travel entries for Ghislaine Maxwell between 1990 and 2020. The document shows frequent international flights, primarily between the U.S. (especially JFK, Miami) and Europe (especially London, Paris), and was generated by CBP Officer Kimberly Meder.

keyFacts: The document is a law enforcement travel log showing 58 border crossing entries for Ghislaine Maxwell from 1990 to 2020.
Maxwell's travel was heavily concentrated between New York (JFK) and London (LHR), with frequent trips to Paris and Miami.
The log was generated on January 16, 2020, by CBP Officer Kimberly Meder, indicating active law enforcement interest in Maxwell's travel patterns at that time.
Travel documents used include U.S. Alien Registration Card (A), Passport (P), and INSPASS (I).
The document is marked 'For Official Use Only / Law Enforcement Sensitive' and is part of the SDNY (Southern District of New York) case materials.
